  "fix_notes": {
    "fix1_eta_min": "v1 used eta_min = lr \u00d7 0.01, making the final LR fraction different across configs (LR=0.1 \u2192 eta=0.001, LR=1e-5 \u2192 eta=1e-7). v2 uses fixed eta_min=1e-06 for all configs so the scheduler decay curve is equivalent.",
    "fix2_divergence": "v1 detected divergence only by loss > 1e10, which gradient clipping (norm=5.0) prevented. Many diverged configs were silently misclassified as underfitting. v2 uses three criteria: loss > 100000000.0 (post-clip), pre-clip grad norm > 10000.0, parameter norm > 1000000.0.",
    "fix3_heatmap": "v1 set inf\u219210.0 for diverged cells, making them indistinguishable from L2=10.0 runs in the colormap. v2 uses nan\u2192black (set_bad='black') for confirmed diverged cells and annotates them 'DIV', entirely separate from the L2 colormap range.",
    "fix4_runtime": "v1 silently ran 100k-epoch configs (up to ~12hr each on RTX 3050). v2 prints estimated runtime warning before starting and offers FAST_MODE=True to skip 100k column.",
    "fix5_seeds": "v1 used single seed per config. v2 uses 2 seeds. Configs where seeds disagree on regime (convergence vs underfitting vs divergence) are flagged 'uncertain=True' in the results."
  },
